angular-v20-signals.content:
Signals are a new reactive primitive in Angular v20. They let you track changes and auto-update views without manual subscriptions.

```ts
import { signal } from '@angular/core';
const count = signal(0);
count.set(count() + 1);
```

dependency-injection-angular-v20.content:
Angular v20 introduces `inject()` for cleaner service injection, especially in standalone components and signals.

```ts
import { inject } from '@angular/core';
import { MyService } from './my.service';
const service = inject(MyService);
```

angular-v20-testing.content:
Use TestBed for component testing and HttpClientTestingModule for API tests.

```ts
beforeEach(() => {
  TestBed.configureTestingModule({ declarations: [AppComponent] });
});
```

getting-started-angular-v20-1.content:
Angular v20 introduces powerful improvements such as signals, the `inject()` function, and better SSR support. This tutorial will guide you through the setup and the first steps.

## 1. Installation

First, make sure you have Node.js 18+ installed. Then install the Angular CLI:

```bash install.sh
npm install -g @angular/cli@20
```

Now create a new project:

```bash
ng new my-app --standalone
cd my-app
```

## 2. First Component

Angular v20 defaults to standalone components. Let’s create the `AppComponent`:

```typescript app.component.ts
import { Component } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  template: '<h1>Hello Angular V20</h1>'
})
export class AppComponent {}
```

Run the dev server:

```bash
ng serve
```

## 3. Using Signals

Signals provide fine-grained reactivity without RxJS boilerplate. Define a signal and update it:

```typescript counter.ts
import { signal } from '@angular/core';

export const counter = signal(0);
counter.set(counter() + 1);
```

Use it inside your component template:

```html app.component.html
<button (click)="counter.set(counter() + 1)">Increment</button>
<p>Value: {{ counter() }}</p>
```

## 4. Dependency Injection with `inject()`

The new `inject()` function replaces constructor injection in many cases:

```typescript my.component.ts
import { Component, inject } from '@angular/core';
import { MyService } from './my.service';

@Component({
  selector: 'my-comp',
  template: '{{ service.message }}'
})
export class MyComponent {
  service = inject(MyService);
}
```

## 5. Routing for SSR

Angular v20 supports SSR-ready routing. Configure routes in `app.routes.ts`:

```typescript app.routes.ts
import { Routes } from '@angular/router';
import { HomeComponent } from './home.component';

export const routes: Routes = [
  { path: '', component: HomeComponent },
  { path: 'articles/:slug', loadComponent: () => import('./article/article.component').then(m => m.ArticleComponent) }
];
```
With these steps, you now have a fully working Angular v20 app, complete with signals, modern DI, and SSR-ready routing.

